00:27:53,551 --> 00:27:54,951
The other one was a more traditional,

592
00:27:55,231 --> 00:27:56,272
merit-based bonus plan,

593
00:27:56,292 --> 00:27:57,832
was they gave the students tests at the beginning of the year

594
00:27:57,852 --> 00:27:58,412
and the end of the year,

595
00:27:58,432 --> 00:27:59,493
and if they got to a certain level,

596
00:28:00,013 --> 00:28:01,073
then the teachers got a bonus.

597
00:28:01,734 --> 00:28:04,775
Then group three got $10,000 at the beginning of the year,

598
00:28:05,455 --> 00:28:06,095
and they told them,

599
00:28:06,775 --> 00:28:08,236
if the students don't reach this test score,

600
00:28:08,256 --> 00:28:08,976
you have to give it back.

601
00:28:10,977 --> 00:28:12,157
And of the three groups,

602
00:28:12,317 --> 00:28:13,877
only group number three actually showed

603
00:28:13,917 --> 00:28:14,938
any improvement in test scores.

604
00:28:19,248 --> 00:28:22,688
So, you know, there's a couple of issues with this study

605
00:28:22,708 --> 00:28:24,729
and I always teach these things with a grain of salt.

